Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the characterization of the region of all points of a convex polygon that can be reached by a point robot moving with bounded curvature. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the motion planning of a point robot. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm to compute the reachable region. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the characterization of the region of all points that can be reached by a point robot, which can be seen as a game between the robot and the polygon. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the motion planning of a point robot with bounded curvature, which can be seen as a control problem.
